column4: But my computer is dead. I pressed the button in the back. The button on the computer does nothing.
What should I do?
button in the back - on the power supply, or the general on off button
It is off, it wont come on.
button in the back - on the power supply, or the general on off button
No response...
button in the back - the one on the power supply, or the general on / off button for your PC that you normally use
It does nothing, just makes a click. No fan, no noise, nothing.
I'll ask you one more time - READ the question I'm asking
button in the back - the one on the power supply, or the general on / off button for your PC that you normally use
Neither works. I turned it off with the button in the back. But no neither button does anything...
button in the back - the one on the power supply, or the general on / off button for your PC that you normally use
answer the question
Button in the back = power supply button.
ok - that is normally an on / off switch for the PSU - not the PC
so what I suggest you do is flick it one more time, then press your normal on/off button on the front
Nothing happens:(
if that does noting, flick the PSU switch again and press the on / off button on the front
how's it looking after you've flicked the switch again and pressed the front bit
No sound, no ligth, nothing happesn. I take the psu button off, try power button in front, nothing. Then turn it the other side, then power button in the front, still nothing.
sounds like a dead component then, contact a PC repair guy
or try one of the hardware channels such as ##hardware suggested
what ever - your current situation can not be fixed by this channel,
we have given you advice on how to progress it, or you can find your own way
